	declarationHtml={`You are a <span style="color: var(--color-gold);">beloved son</span> or <span style="color: var(--color-gold);">daughter</span>.<br />Not a slave. Not a servant. Not a tool. Not a performer.`}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for church staff`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The answer to an overlooked, overworked staff is not a better org chart, a bigger title, or more discipline. It is not even a stronger devotional habit as one more task on the list. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a holy Father for a beloved son or daughter who happens to run the database, the budget, or the soundboard.</p><p>You spend your weeks serving everyone’s ministry but your own soul: setting up, cleaning up, following up, covering the gaps no one sees. But you cannot give a love you are not receiving. Before you were hired, before your name went on the staff page, before your first Sunday, you were a child of God — and that is still the truest thing about you.</p><p>So you clock in tomorrow not first as staff, and not first to finish the list — but to be <em>loved</em> by your Father. The work is what overflows after. He is not auditing your task list; He is delighting in His child. The one who keeps the church running, at last, is kept by the Father.</p>`}
