	keepReadingHtml={`Begin with the <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">whole Bible free online with audio</a>, learn <a href="/the-fathers-heart-bible/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">why the Father’s Heart Bible™ exists</a>, or get oriented with our <a href="/guides/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Bible reading guides</a> — including <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how to pray</a> and <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a>. Or meet fellow workers in <a href="/bible-for/pastors/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">the Bible for pastors</a>, <a href="/bible-for/worship-leaders/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">worship leaders</a>, and <a href="/bible-for/student-ministry/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">student ministry</a>.`}
	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for discouraged or unappreciated church staff?`, answer: `Colossians 3:23 (work heartily, as for the Father, not for men), Hebrews 6:10 (God will not overlook your work and love), Matthew 6:4 (your Father sees in secret and rewards), Galatians 6:9 (don't grow weary of doing good), and Matthew 11:28 (come to Me and rest) all speak directly to staff who feel unseen. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to someone who feels overlooked in ministry?`, answer: `Scripture is clear that God sees what people miss. Hebrews 6:10 says He is not unjust and will not overlook your work and the love you've shown in serving. Matthew 6:4 promises your Father sees in secret and rewards. Your value never depended on being noticed by people. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you can read these passages free, with audio, and meet a Father who sees every unseen hour.` },
		{ question: `How can church staff avoid burnout?`, answer: `Burnout grows when staff pour out without first being filled — and when ministry guilt makes rest feel like failure. Staff who last tend to receive before they give (Matthew 11:28), refuse to let productivity define their worth (Luke 10:42 — one thing is necessary), and remember they work for a Father, not a crowd (Colossians 3:23). Many begin by reading the Father's Heart Bible™ daily simply to be fathered, not to prep for Sunday.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free online Bible with audio for church staff?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on any phone or computer and read or hear any book, useful for a quick word before a long workday or simply being fathered in the middle of the week.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for church staff?`, answer: `It is the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so the One you serve all week has a Father's face. For staff, that reframes everything: you come to the text first as a beloved son or daughter being fathered, not only as a worker preparing the next thing.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about resting when ministry never stops?`, answer: `Rest in Scripture is not laziness — it is trust. Jesus invites the heavy-laden to come to Him for rest (Matthew 11:28), and He gently tells busy Martha that one thing is necessary (Luke 10:42). Even the people who keep the church running need to sit at the Father's feet. The Father's Heart Bible™ lets you hear those passages as a Father's invitation, free with audio.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to a church staff member who wants to quit?`, answer: `You are in good company — even Elijah, after great service, sat down under a tree and asked God to take his life (1 Kings 19). God did not rebuke him; He let him sleep, fed him, and spoke gently in a whisper. If you're at that point, the Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read that story and Jesus' invitation to the weary (Matthew 11:28) free, with audio — and meet a Father who restores His servants rather than discarding them.` },
	]}
	ctaBottomHeading={`Be fathered before you serve`}
	ctaBottomBodyHtml={`Watch the story behind the Father’s Heart Bible™ — the translation that lets you meet the One you serve as Father. Then come and be filled, so what you pour out all week overflows from what you’ve received.`}
